DSA-007

### What is Block Scope?

> A block is anything inside { } curly braces.
> 
> 
> Variables declared **inside a block** `{}` can only be accessed **within that block**.
> 

---

### ðŸ”¤ Java Code Example:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a = 10;

        {
            int b = 20;
            System.out.println(a); // âœ… a is accessible here
            System.out.println(b); // âœ… b is accessible here
        }

        System.out.println(a); // âœ… a is accessible
        // System.out.println(b); âŒ Error: b is not visible here
    }
}
```

ðŸ“Œ `b` is only accessible **inside the inner block** where itâ€™s declared.

